1
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,720
You settle the bill later.

2
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,320
Fifty per person, no more.

3
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,240
Director, come on...

4
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:42,400
Anything over, I'll cover it.

5
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,400
What do you mean, you'll cover it?

6
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,320
It just can't go over.

7
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,680
Fine.

8
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,800
Lin Yiran,

9
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,280
you could learn a bit of Taozi's laziness.

10
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,840
How am I lazy?

11
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:00,680
Don't interrupt.

12
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,840
Don't work so hard.

13
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,920
Don't take it so seriously.

14
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,720
Take things too seriously,

15
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:11,080
and you're the one who suffers.

16
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:15,120
You have your own ideas,

17
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:18,080
town leaders have their angle,

18
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,840
county leaders have their vantage point.

19
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,600
Everyone considers different things.

20
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,520
It won't bend to your will.

21
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:28,840
Patience brings perfection.

22
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,960
Slowing down is a good thing.

23
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,960
Honestly, what upsets me most

24
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,760
isn't the China Chic Zone being canceled.

25
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,280
Sure, I'm sad it can't happen,

26
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,640
but what upsets me most

27
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,760
is Secretary Peng's attitude.

28
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,440
What's wrong with her attitude?

29
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,520
Yiran, you...

30
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,080
you're just too naive,

31
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,720
too childish.

32
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,960
Secretary Peng was showing you firsthand,

33
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,520
teaching you a vivid lesson.

34
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,920
Work is work.

35
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,560
Don't drag feelings into it.

36
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,560
Only people going nowhere like me and Taozi

37
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,640
would sit here and talk feelings with you.

38
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,360
Director, just talk about the matter.

39
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,520
Don't rope me in.

40
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,640
Who's going nowhere?

41
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:15,600
Taozi,

42
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,160
but Director Liao's right about one thing.

43
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,960
Naive, childish.

44
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,840
Secretary Peng needs someone who charges ahead.

45
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,920
But when push really comes to shove,

46
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:28,160
she can't protect you either.

47
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,200
What nonsense are you spouting?

48
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,080
You've twisted a good message all wrong.

49
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,280
Fine, I'm a crooked-mouthed monk.

50
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,440
I can't recite the scriptures right.

51
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,280
Secretary Peng,

52
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,360
she likes you,

53
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,040
supports you,

54
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,040
because

55
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,640
the work needs it,

56
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,920
the organization needs it,

57
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,080
and on a larger scale,

58
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,560
the people need it.

59
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,680
She's

60
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:51,800
giving you a chance to hone yourself.

61
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,040
Director Liao,

62
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,800
that patronizing tone is slipping out again.

63
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,080
My bad, my bad.

64
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:56,960
I talked too much.

65
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:57,800
Come on, come on.

66
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,360
All right, all right.

67
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,040
We finally got out together.

68
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:00,760
Let's stop talking about it.

69
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,320
Let's raise a glass together, okay?

70
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,120
Okay, come on, cheers.

71
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:03,800
Let's celebrate.

72
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:04,760
To us,

73
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,200
happy disbanding.

74
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,080
Come on.

75
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,560
Lin Yiran, are you really mad at me?

76
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,680
Come on, we're just waiting on you.

77
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,240
Why should it be?

78
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,320
What do you mean, why?

79
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,760
Why must the Four Treasures of the Study

80
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:23,120
Cultural Festival be done their way?

81
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,240
Why must the Four Treasures Cultural Festival

82
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,280
have to be approved by industry insiders?

83
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,080
The previous festivals

84
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,520
were just insiders entertaining themselves.

85
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:35,400
Money was spent,

86
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,040
but nothing came of it.

87
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,680
So...

88
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:40,240
Why can't we try a different approach?

89
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,240
If a different approach

90
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,920
brings traffic to Taohua Town,

91
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,360
and profits to the people,

92
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,680
why shouldn't we do it?

93
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,520
There goes your stubborn streak again.

94
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,320
Xuan Yan.

95
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,040
What do you think?

96
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,200
It's a false dilemma.

97
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:55,760
Look,

98
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:59,920
my dad insists on making traditional Xuan paper.

99
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:00,920
Just over this one thing,

100
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,880
we've fought countless times.

101
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,040
You've all seen it.

102
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:05,080
So how is their current mindset

103
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,560
any different from my dad's?

104
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,240
I still stand by

105
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,800
my own point of view.

106
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,760
Brush and ink must move with the times.

107
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,160
Only what consumers love has value.

108
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,720
No matter what industry,

109
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,720
it must evolve with changing

110
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,720
consumer mindsets.

111
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,800
What stays is the original vision and cultural heritage.

112
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,800
They insist on clinging to the old traditions

113
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,640
And what's the end result?

114
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,760
The only outcome is they'll personally

115
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,080
push the industry and culture

116
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,640
straight into the fire

117
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:35,120
Exactly

118
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,000
Deputy Mayor Luo and the others

119
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,080
totally confused me with their talk

120
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,400
The way they played off each other

121
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,360
No way

122
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,240
We prepared so well for the Four Treasures of the Study Cultural Festival

123
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,640
We can't just let it go like this

124
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,920
What are you planning to do?

125
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,960
This is a Party Committee resolution

126
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,200
A decision by the Party organization

127
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,440
You can't just act on impulse

128
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,680
The Director is right

129
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,560
If you do this

130
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,720
you'd be crossing the line

131
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,800
I think the Party Committee team

132
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,800
is also influenced by the higher-ups

133
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,680
Then I'll go to the higher-up leaders

134
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,360
I'll do all my homework

135
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,880
I'll lay out the reasoning clearly

136
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,320
Maybe the leaders' attitude will shift

137
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,440
This is absolutely absurd

138
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:09,120
Going over their heads is a huge taboo

139
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,240
You silly girl

140
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,120
Teacher Liao, Teacher Liao

141
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,520
Mind your leadership image

142
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,520
She's beyond teaching

143
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,360
It's fine, it's fine

144
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,000
Here, let me order more skewers

145
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,680
Don't order more, we're all full

146
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,560
I'll eat a bit more

147
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,680
It's fine, really, it's fine

148
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,960
Yiran, if you really do this

149
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,320
you'll offend every single member

150
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,320
of the whole leadership team

151
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,080
And then you'll have nowhere to go

152
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,680
She'd have no options left

153
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,240
If she really dares to do this

154
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:35,720
in Taohua Town

155
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,960
she won't even have a place to stand

156
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,680
Alright

157
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,320
I get it

158
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,120
This is no child's play

159
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,120
In this area

160
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,240
Taozi and I

161
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,880
could both be your teachers

162
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,160
I love my teacher

163
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,640
but

164
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,560
I love the truth even more

165
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,240
Come on

166
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,000
Eat

167
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:57,920
Eat

168
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,520
Actually

169
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:06,360
I only care whether this can be done

170
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,320
As for me personally

171
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,320
let's leave it at that

172
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,680
Xuan Yan

173
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,000
Those two don't approve of me anymore anyway

174
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,760
What about you?

175
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,320
They don't approve

176
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,720
but I support you

177
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,440
Better to die standing than live kneeling

178
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,440
Let the crumbling of heaven and earth

179
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,560
be the beating drums of your battlefield.

180
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,080
Fight

181
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,600
Fight

182
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,880
Secretary Peng.

183
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,000
You...

184
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,760
came all the way here to wait for me?

185
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:30,880
What else?

186
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,200
This was my own decision.

187
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,559
It has nothing to do with you.

188
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,760
Lin Yiran.

189
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:44,120
Do you think that at yesterday's meeting,

190
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,520
I caved under pressure

191
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,440
and threw you under the bus?

192
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,720
Lin Yiran.

193
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,960
I said I'd be your strong backing.

194
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,760
That has never changed.

195
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,240
In yesterday's situation,

196
00:08:57,800 --> 00:09:00,000
if I hadn't reined you in beforehand,

197
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,560
if I hadn't stopped you in time,

198
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:04,520
knowing you as "Lin the Firebrand,"

199
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,000
you'd have flipped the table right there.

200
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,120
If you truly offended the town Party committee,

201
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:13,240
the consequences of many things

202
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,800
would be more than you could bear.

203
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,240
I'm sorry, Secretary Peng.

204
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:22,640
See?

205
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,720
You shouldn't have acted out like this today.

206
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:27,520
Running to the county committee to see the leaders?

207
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:30,240
Where does that leave the town Party committee?

208
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,120
You can't be this impulsive.

209
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,600
You're a cadre in a leadership post now.

210
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,800
If you can't endure and bear the burden,

211
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,440
you won't get far.

212
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,640
I'm not being impulsive.

213
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,560
And I'm not just enduring humiliation.

214
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,080
I just feel that with this matter,

215
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,320
as long as I can do it well,

216
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,200
bring value to Taohua Town,

217
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,960
and give the people a better life,

218
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,320
then it's worth doing.

219
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,560
Even at the cost of your own future?

220
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,120
Of course I don't want that.

221
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,400
But if there's no other way,

222
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,000
this is all I can do.

223
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,280
Thank you, Secretary Peng, for looking out for me.

224
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,000
But I may

225
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,960
have to let you down after all.

226
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,360
I stayed up all night to prepare

227
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,720
a full analysis report on the China Chic Zone.

228
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,920
What needs to be said, I still have to say.

229
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,400
Those I need to offend,

230
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,880
I still have to offend.

231
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:24,560
Well, the young lady's quite stubborn.

232
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,640
All right. Let's go.

233
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:26,800
You don't need to come with me.

234
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,520
I don't want to drag you down.

235
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,000
Not only stubborn,

236
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,720
but loyal too.

237
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,920
Lin Yiran, you know what?

238
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:42,400
Today you crossed a forbidden red line.

239
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,880
There's no way I'd let you go alone.

240
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,920
Not now,

241
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:48,840
and from now on,

242
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,120
never.

243
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,520
Don't worry.

244
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,600
With me taking you in today,

245
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,400
things will be different.

246
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,280
Let's go.

247
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:57,960
No.

248
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,400
But for a committee member like you,

249
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:01,720
it's not appropriate.

250
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,760
Precisely because I'm now the top Party leader,

251
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,920
I can handle it.

252
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:09,480
Lin Yiran.

253
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,160
I've already helped you into the saddle.

254
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,560
Let me ride with you a little further.

255
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:17,520
Let's go.

256
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:39,120
The county leaders' approval in principle today

257
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,600
was really because of your drive,

258
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:44,880
your will to act and get things done,

259
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,320
that moved the leadership.

260
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:47,880
You have to understand,

261
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:50,000
it's not easy for them to make such a call.

262
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:50,840
Think about it,

263
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:53,720
so much of this is still in the planning stage.

264
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,400
Can you carry it out?

265
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,280
How far can you carry it out?

266
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,160
What results will it bring?

267
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,880
It's all unknown.

268
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,480
I understand.

269
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,520
Secretary Peng, rest assured.

270
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,240
I'll do my very best

271
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:08,640
to consider every detail and issue,

272
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,880
and strive for perfection.

273
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:11,320
Good.

274
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,160
Xiao Wu, pull over.

275
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,160
Secretary Peng.

276
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,120
Weren't you rushing back for a meeting?

277
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,960
Let me buy you a coffee.

278
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:27,960
Secretary Peng.

279
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:29,840
Thank you.

280
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,040
Xiao Lin, what do you think?

281
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:41,120
Our sandy-field rice looks beautiful, doesn't it?

282
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:42,920
It's beautiful.

283
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:43,720
Actually,

284
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,880
I'm feeling quite sentimental today.

285
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,400
You know,

286
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:51,240
sometimes when I look at you,

287
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,200
it's like seeing myself over 20 years ago,

288
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,960
just starting out on the job.

289
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,120
Back then,

290
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,600
I was just like you.

291
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,720
Light in my eyes, dreams in my heart.

292
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,800
Ready to take on heaven and earth,

293
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,520
afraid of nothing.

294
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,120
I felt the whole world was mine,

295
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,280
like a blank canvas,

296
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,640
where I could paint freely as I pleased.

297
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,240
Time really flies.

298
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,600
Now, along our Southern Anhui scenic route,

299
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,160
the most profitable

300
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,040
and most creative restaurants,

301
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:23,640
village cafes and homestays,

302
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,360
are all run by young people.

303
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:29,040
Young people today are truly amazing.

304
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:30,920
Sometimes,

305
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,960
just one small creative idea from them

306
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,360
can change the world,

307
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,840
leading the rhythm of the times,

308
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,040
opening up new opportunities.

309
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:41,480
Lin Yiran,

310
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,520
charge forward bravely.

311
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,320
Win or lose,

312
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,160
youth itself

313
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,720
is the most moving masterpiece of all.

314
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,120
Director Huang.

315
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:39,360
Director Lin.

316
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,880
I heard you've been swamped over there.

317
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:43,360
I was thinking of dropping by to check on you.

318
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,120
But I was afraid I'd interrupt your work.

319
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,480
Come on, Director Huang.

320
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,720
That sounds so fake.

321
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:50,040
I called you and you didn't pick up.

322
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,400
Didn't reply to my WeChat either.

323
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:54,000
The county audit bureau's been at our place.

324
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,200
Camped out for days now.

325
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,600
Grinding away morning to night.

326
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,800
I haven't had a spare moment.

327
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:58,800
I heard about it.

328
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,880
Just a routine audit, right?

329
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:00,400
Yeah, exactly.

330
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:02,520
That's why I had Little Fan from your office

331
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:03,840
head back the very next day.

332
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,000
Now a lot of people are gossiping about me.

333
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,520
Saying I'm sucking up to you, the money god.

334
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,360
Well, thanks for understanding!

335
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,880
I haven't even had a chance to thank you.

336
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:12,520
I'm just really anxious right now.

337
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:14,200
The funding for the China Chic Zone.

338
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,840
Four themes, lots of setups all needing money.

339
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:17,960
If you don't get me the money soon,

340
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:18,800
I really won't make it in time.

341
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:19,880
You don't even need to tell me.

342
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:21,240
That last hundred-plus thousand in special funds,

343
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,720
I already allocated it all in one go.

344
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,520
Allocated?

345
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:27,800
We've all heard about your heroic feat.

346
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,400
Secretary Peng charged into the county committee with you.

347
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:32,520
Turning the tide against all odds,

348
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,120
saving the day from total collapse!

349
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,600
Before you two even got back,

350
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,240
the rumors had already spread.

351
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,800
It's already become the talk of the town.

352
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,880
Just between us, okay?

353
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,880
The town party secretary personally stepped in,

354
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,720
and got the county leadership's approval.

355
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,040
How could Deputy Mayor Luo dare to stall anymore?

356
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:50,640
He signed off half an hour ago.

357
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,960
Transferred it all to him in one shot.

358
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,160
He... he didn't even tell me.

359
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:56,160
You don't know yet?

360
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,400
Secretary Peng rushed off as soon as she got back,

361
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,200
straight to the Xiaoling scenic rural road.

362
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,320
Apparently there's this one household.

363
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,240
The demolition compensation was all agreed on,

364
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,840
but they kicked up a fuss the moment work started.

365
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,880
Deputy Mayor Luo and Director Ge all went over.

366
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,520
Alright.

367
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,640
Thanks, Director Huang, I...

368
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,000
Good food is worth the wait for you,

369
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,040
but the cafeteria won't wait!

370
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,280
Hurry up and go grab a bite.

371
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,360
Thank you, Director Huang.

372
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,320
You're way too busy.

373
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,840
Ma'am, sir,

374
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,920
our government's work

375
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,120
still needs your full support.

376
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,160
Secretary Peng,

377
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,680
it's not that we don't support it.

378
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,680
You know how it is.

379
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,520
My legs aren't in good shape,

380
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,560
and the kids have grown up.

381
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,120
Director Ge,

382
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:35,320
look at how Secretary Peng treats Lin Yiran.

383
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:38,040
She's truly done everything she can.

384
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,120
It's so good, there's just...

385
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,520
nothing more to say.

386
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,920
It's all for the sake of the work.

387
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:44,840
But you should know,

388
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:47,000
the county leadership team

389
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,880
only agreed in principle.

390
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:52,000
If something goes wrong along the way...

391
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,760
Don't worry so much over nothing.

392
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:56,640
If the higher-ups dared to give the go-ahead,

393
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:58,240
on the big picture and main principles,

394
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,320
there's no major fault.

395
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,880
I understand that.

396
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,560
But look at Lin Yiran and her young crew,

397
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:03,880
what on earth are they cooking up?

398
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,720
Who's ever seen anything like it?

399
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,400
Right?

400
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,040
Brother, I'm only saying this out of concern.

401
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,040
Let me say a couple of things I shouldn't.

402
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:15,000
Since Secretary Peng supports Lin Yiran so much,

403
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,720
you should also give her some advice.

404
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,760
She should think about herself now and then.

405
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:19,319
Right?

406
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,520
I really shouldn't be saying this,

407
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:23,240
but...

408
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:25,040
Officials, have some tea.

409
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:25,520
Uncle,

410
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,200
thank you.

411
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,119
Sorry to trouble you.

412
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,960
We're putting you out.

413
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:29,880
No, not at all.

414
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,200
Don't mention it, don't mention it.

415
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,640
My wife here,

416
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,240
she can't get used to those county-town apartments.

417
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,400
She just wants to come back.

418
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,200
Have Secretary Peng have a word with her,

419
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,600
and it'll all be fine, won't it?

420
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,520
Yes, yes.

421
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:43,400
My wife loves listening to Secretary Peng talk.

422
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,400
Reasonable and heartfelt.

423
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,840
Right, right, right.

424
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,600
Well, you carry on with your work.

425
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,400
Okay, okay.

426
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:55,960
"Do nothing, make no mistakes; do more, make more mistakes."

427
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,320
There's something wrong with that saying,

428
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:58,560
but I think...

429
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:00,320
whatever exists has its reason.

430
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:03,240
If problems really arise,

431
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,760
it'll be too late.

432
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,400
That reminds me of something.

433
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,520
Your mother-in-law,

434
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,240
she passed from cancer last year, right?

435
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,600
Lung cancer.

436
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:14,920
There was this one time,

437
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,240
I heard the director of the oncology hospital say

438
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:18,880
that among cancer patients,

439
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:20,480
60 to 70 percent

440
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,640
don't actually die from the disease.

441
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,320
Then why?

442
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:25,400
They're scared to death.

443
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:27,000
Isn't that right?

444
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,240
Really?

445
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:31,720
Scared to death.

446
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:33,000
How'd it go, Secretary?

447
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,240
How was the chat?

448
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,160
Pretty good.

449
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:36,520
What do you mean?

450
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,240
Come, sit.

451
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:37,800
Okay, okay, okay.

452
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:40,760
Just take a look.

453
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,920
What are these things?

454
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:46,840
Slow down there.

455
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,360
Where does this go?

456
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,240
Put it over there.

457
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:49,920
Okay.

458
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,600
Just leave it here for now.

459
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,480
Yiran.

460
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,880
Who set all this up?

461
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,000
Who else could it be?

462
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:00,800
Yiran.

463
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:03,600
Our Four Treasures of the Study Cultural Festival

464
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,400
is going all out, huh?

465
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:06,520
This...

466
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:07,720
What are you talking about?

467
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,600
Where'd we get this kind of budget?

468
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,520
The only reasonable explanation

469
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:15,960
is the strong attention from city and county leaders

470
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,440
and their heartfelt support.

471
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,320
How much did all this cost?

472
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:21,080
It's money down the drain.

473
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,960
Money thrown away.

474
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:23,960
Let me ask you.

475
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,760
Do you know how much this stage

476
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:27,040
costs? Take a guess.

477
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:30,480
Rented, five thousand a day.

478
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:32,120
Deputy Mayor Luo picked it himself.

479
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,600
Wait, wait, hold on.

480
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:36,080
This one? Five thousand?

481
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:36,840
That's right.

482
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,920
Why do I have a bad feeling about this?

483
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,600
We're still five days from opening.

484
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,560
Deputy Mayor Luo set it up this early?

485
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,440
How much extra will that cost?

486
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,360
Our funds are already tight.

487
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,760
How can we afford him blowing it like this?

488
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,600
I'm not done yet.

489
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,240
This high-end sound system,

490
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,000
ten thousand a day.

491
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,240
What? Ten thousand? Ten thousand?

492
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,920
This one? Ten thousand?

493
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:01,600
Buddy, buddy, buddy.

494
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:02,760
We've got all this stuff here,

495
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:03,800
and there are still several days to go.

496
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,720
Did you get the date wrong?

497
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,040
Nope.

498
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,720
Booked last-minute last night.

499
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:09,920
For today.

500
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,280
When we set the budget,

501
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:17,000
I specifically told Deputy Mayor Luo

502
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:19,360
that we don't need this stage at all.

503
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,360
Just a red carpet would do.

504
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,120
And we don't need this sound system either.

505
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:24,760
Why would Deputy Mayor Luo do this?

506
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:25,960
Who knows?

507
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:28,040
Wait, sis.

508
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,360
Did the finance office give extra funding?

509
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,240
No way.

510
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:33,600
You know how much the special funds are.

511
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:35,160
Deputy Mayor Luo is here.

512
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:41,960
Perfect timing.

513
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:43,480
Everyone's here, right?

514
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:45,160
Urgent mission.

515
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,520
Listen up, urgent mission.

516
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:48,480
A top city official is coming.

517
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,160
He's doing an inspection.

518
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,600
He decided last-minute to visit our prep site.

519
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:51,440
To take a look.

520
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:53,120
So, you see...

521
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,040
Now you know why, right?

522
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:56,520
Here's your answer.

523
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,480
Got it, got it, got it.

524
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,800
Wait, what answer?

525
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:03,600
Never mind the answer.

526
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,800
Everyone listen to me now.

527
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,560
Lin Yiran.

528
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:06,760
When the officials arrive,

529
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:07,800
they'll give a rallying speech.

530
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,440
Go notify the nearby merchants right away.

531
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:09,920
Get them over here.

532
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:11,360
Liven up the atmosphere.

533
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:13,840
Also, water, badges, uniforms.

534
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,000
The supplies have arrived.

535
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,000
Zhang Bin, Wang Hao.

536
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:16,720
Grab a few people.

537
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,000
Move the supplies in a bit.

538
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,720
The rest of you, use your eyes and pitch in!

539
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:23,160
Clean this place up.

540
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:23,960
All right?

541
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,000
What is today, exactly?

542
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,160
A surprise drill.

543
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,120
It's a test to see if our team

544
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:31,280
can really handle tough battles.

545
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:32,000
So, everyone,

546
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,840
show me your best game face.

547
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,160
Let the officials see

548
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,920
our ability, our standard.

549
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,720
Okay, get moving!

550
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,560
Come on, come on.

551
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,280
Director Liao.

552
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,600
Are your legs hurting or what?

553
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,120
Get moving!

554
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,240
You're a veteran Party member.

555
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,960
Shouldn't you set an example now?

556
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:54,800
Take the lead!

557
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,160
Lead what?

558
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,480
Make ourselves a laughingstock?

559
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:00,480
Look at you.

560
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,680
You, you're always like this.

561
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:04,200
Regardless of time or place,

562
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,440
you just spout nonsense.

563
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,080
You really should take a hard look at yourself.

564
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,400
Are you still a Party member?

565
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:09,920
A Party cadre?

566
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,120
Of course I am.

567
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,440
Then you should obey the organization.

568
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,000
Follow your superior's arrangements.

569
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:18,600
As Taohua Town's Deputy Mayor in charge,

570
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,960
of the Four Treasures of the Study Cultural Festival,

571
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,480
and Deputy Head of the leading group,

572
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:22,720
can I lead you or not?

573
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:23,960
Can I command you or not?

574
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,680
It's not about commanding.

575
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,280
By doing this,

576
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,840
have you thought about the consequences?

577
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:30,760
I don't care about consequences.

578
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:31,280
I'm just asking,

579
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,160
can I command you or not?

580
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:37,800
Yes.

581
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,720
Yes? Then get moving!

582
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,320
Go move the water, hurry!

583
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,360
As if I can't handle you.

584
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,240
Director Liao.

585
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:46,960
Liao...

586
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:48,920
Wait, Lin Yiran!

587
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,920
Why are you still standing here?

588
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,240
Go rally the merchants!

589
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:52,720
Hurry!

590
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,440
I can't command you either, huh?

591
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:56,520
Fine.

592
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,200
Deputy Mayor Luo, let me ask you something.

593
00:22:58,520 --> 00:22:59,840
Director Huang already said

594
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,520
you took the special funds.

595
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,160
My China Chic Zone needs the money urgently.

596
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:03,960
Where's the money?

597
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,400
Oh my god.

598
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,720
The officials are about to arrive!

599
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:09,520
It's a crisis and you're asking me for money?

600
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,720
Let's get past this first, okay?

601
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,280
Well, isn't my situation urgent too?

602
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,000
Don't I need the money?

603
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,480
Fine, fine, fine.

604
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:15,520
Go notify the merchants, now.

605
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:17,440
I still have to...

606
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:17,880
Hurry!

607
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,800
Get more people!

608
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,640
Look at all of them...

609
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:25,200
Everyone, move faster!

610
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:30,320
Yiran

611
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,800
Are you really going to ask the vendors?

612
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:35,160
They'll chew you out alive.

613
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,600
Secretary Peng specifically told me

614
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,960
to follow orders from above.

615
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:41,440
To maintain unity.

616
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,560
To bear the burden with patience.

617
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:44,800
This is really killing me.

618
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,240
Alright, don't come get yelled at with me.

619
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:47,200
Hurry back.

620
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:48,320
I'm off.

621
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,080
The Xuan paper festival is all about this stuff.

622
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,080
Building stages, putting on shows, wasting money.

623
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:58,680
We thought once Director Lin came,

624
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:01,200
you'd do something real and practical for us.

625
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,280
Who would've thought,

626
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:03,600
you'd start pulling this stuff too.

627
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:06,360
Asking us to come play along in your show,

628
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,720
to be your extras.

629
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,520
You've really made a joke of it.

630
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:12,120
If the leaders care, we get more support.

631
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,960
It's good for us too, right?

632
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,360
Let's all cooperate a little.

633
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:17,520
It really won't take much of your time.

634
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,720
Don't feed us that line.

635
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:19,560
If the leaders truly care,

636
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:20,920
they'd do something real.

637
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,200
Not all this empty showboating.

638
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:22,840
Right.

639
00:24:22,840 --> 00:24:23,560
Little Lin,

640
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,200
when you first came here,

641
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,000
running around for us,

642
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,160
we all saw it.

643
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,440
We even said among ourselves,

644
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,600
this girl's got it tough.

645
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,000
She's genuinely working for us.

646
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,480
We shouldn't make things hard for her.

647
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,960
We'll cooperate whenever we can.

648
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,520
Now that you're the director,

649
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,520
now that you're a leader,

650
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,400
your original heart shouldn't change, right?

651
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,520
I really am sorry, everyone.

652
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:41,560
It really is my fault.

653
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,440
I'm sorry.

654
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:44,760
I'm sorry.

655
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,840
I don't think Little Lin is that kind of person.

656
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,520
If she came to ask us,

657
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,920
she must have her own reasons.

658
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,720
Let's just go, it won't waste much time.

659
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,520
Right?

660
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:57,240
Like we said before,

661
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,080
let's support Little Lin's work more.

662
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,640
Don't make things too hard for her.

663
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,320
Right?

664
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:02,520
Let's not talk about it anymore.

665
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:03,240
Enough talk.

666
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,120
Okay.

667
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:04,800
Alright.

668
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,440
Thank you, thank you all.

669
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,280
Truly, thank you.

670
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:08,000
I'm sorry.

671
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,080
Little Lin,

672
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:10,520
only because it's you.

673
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,400
If it were anyone else,

674
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,560
I'd have flipped the table.

675
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,040
Alright, alright, alright.

676
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,160
I hope everyone can trust me.

677
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,160
I won't let you all down.

678
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:21,960
I'll definitely make this event

679
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,520
a success for everyone.

680
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:24,760
Good, good.

681
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,240
Come on, come on.

682
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,600
A little more enthusiasm!

683
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:34,840
Sir, thank you for coming.

684
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:35,760
Deputy Mayor Luo.

685
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,040
Thank you so much.

686
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:40,680
Taking time out to check on our work.

687
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:41,880
Come on, everyone.

688
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,560
Let's give a warm round of applause

689
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,000
to welcome our leader.

690
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:49,200
Thank you all for your hard work.

691
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,800
Deputy Mayor Luo's been telling me

692
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,960
your preparations have been excellent.

693
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,800
And very demanding.

694
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:56,680
I was passing by today

695
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:58,400
and decided to drop in on everyone.

696
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,600
Sir, come up on stage, please.

697
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:01,720
No need, no need.

698
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,560
I won't take up much of your time.

699
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:04,320
Sir.

700
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:06,200
How could you be taking up our time?

701
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,600
We've all been looking forward to your visit.

702
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,960
Every single moment.

703
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:11,240
We're eager to hear your guidance.

704
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:12,280
Please, don't say that.

705
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:14,400
I have no guidance to offer.

706
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:15,760
I just came to see everyone.

707
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,640
In a couple of days,

708
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,560
the Four Treasures Cultural Festival begins.

709
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,200
Time is tight, the task is heavy.

710
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,200
I'll just say one thing.

711
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:22,560
I'm hoping to see

712
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:24,480
a smooth, spectacular event

713
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:27,000
that brings real benefits to the people.

714
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:32,200
You all heard what our leader said.

715
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,440
So we need to work even harder.

716
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,160
All right, then.

717
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:36,480
Sir.

718
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,760
These are all our merchant friends here.

719
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:40,800
They came on their own to welcome you.

720
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:42,560
I'd also like to take this chance

721
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,400
to give you a brief report

722
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,440
on our current progress.

723
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,280
And let the merchants hear as well

724
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,560
what we've been doing,

725
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:50,960
what stage we've reached,

726
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:52,560
and what our ultimate goal is.

727
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:53,280
Don't you think

728
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,800
we should let the public know more?

729
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,280
Knowing leads to understanding,

730
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,720
and understanding leads to support.

731
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,480
So I'll begin, then.

732
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,400
To ensure the success

733
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:11,280
of the Four Treasures Cultural Festival,

734
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:13,440
as the deputy head

735
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:15,320
of the festival's leadership group,

736
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:16,840
under the guidance of Town Party Secretary

737
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:19,000
Comrade Peng Ruixue,

738
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:22,320
I've convened seven related meetings,

739
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:25,680
clarifying the meaning and purpose,

740
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:28,080
assigning the related tasks,

741
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:31,080
and coordinating the relevant units.

742
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:32,520
Throughout all this,

743
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,400
there's been sincere care from our leaders,

744
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,680
heartfelt effort from our colleagues,

745
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:40,840
and genuine support from local businesses.

746
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:43,760
I believe this Four Treasures Festival

747
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,920
will be a resounding success,

748
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,520
a triumphant event.

749
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,520
Keep it brief, keep it brief.

750
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:51,920
Deputy Mayor Luo speaks well.

751
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,040
But talk alone isn't enough.

752
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,040
You must act as well.

753
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:55,240
In a couple of days,

754
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:57,160
I'll come inspect your work in person.

755
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,160
Rest assured, sir.

756
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,760
We'll complete the task successfully.

757
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,560
All right, I need to get back to work.

758
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:02,640
You all have work to do too.

759
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:03,760
I won't bother you any longer.

760
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:04,840
As I said before,

761
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,400
I sincerely wish you success.

762
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:07,080
All right.

763
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:08,200
Thank you, sir.

764
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:09,680
Everyone, let's see our leader off.

765
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,320
Deputy Mayor Luo.

766
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,680
I...

767
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:29,960
Oh, right.

768
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,280
Everyone,

769
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:33,000
thank you all for coming today.

770
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:34,920
We won't keep you from your business.

771
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:35,880
You can all head back now.

772
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,000
Thank you, thank you, everyone.

773
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:37,720
Go on, go on.

774
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,920
Deputy Mayor Luo, I'm not finished.

775
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,760
And take off those uniforms too.

776
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:44,760
Don't wear the badges either.

777
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:45,480
You'll get them dirty.

778
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,920
Also, this archway, the stage,

779
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,200
and all the sound equipment, keep an eye on them.

780
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,280
There's a deposit on those.

781
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,200
Deputy Mayor Luo, I wasn't finished.

782
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,200
What do you want?

783
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,880
What about the funding for the China Chic Zone?

784
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,080
Director Huang said he gave it to you. Where's the money?

785
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,520
You can't see where the money went?

786
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:01,520
This huge archway,

787
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,600
the atmosphere, the stage,

788
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,280
and the sound system,

789
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:04,520
which of these doesn't cost money?

790
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,280
No, it's all been spent?

791
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,400
Really?

792
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,960
There's a little left, not much.

793
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:12,320
That was earmarked funding for the event.

794
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,760
Now that's an interesting thing to say.

795
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,800
Which cent did I not spend on this project?

796
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:18,840
I can swear on my life,

797
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:19,520
not a single cent

798
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:20,680
went into my own pocket.

799
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:22,000
If you don't believe me, go investigate me.

800
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:24,760
That was earmarked funding for the China Chic Zone.

801
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,080
Who decided that?

802
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:27,880
You decided it, Lin Yiran?

803
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,640
You get to decide how this money is used?

804
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,800
And I have to listen to you?

805
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:31,680
Get this straight.

806
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:33,240
When you become my superior someday,

807
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,800
then you'll have the right to speak to me like that.

808
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:35,840
Ridiculous.

809
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:36,480
I...

810
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:39,840
What?

811
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:41,280
What are you looking at me for?

812
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,000
Take this back.

813
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:50,000
I'm not finished, Deputy Mayor Luo.

814
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:52,320
Forget it.

815
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:53,600
Just...

816
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:55,520
Wait, Sister Yiran,

817
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,680
so what do we do now?

818
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:29,680
Yiran.

819
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:31,160
Honestly,

820
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:31,960
on this matter,

821
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:33,480
you've already done your best.

822
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,560
Everyone can see that.

823
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,720
Doing your best is enough.

824
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:41,040
I just don't understand.

825
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:46,040
Why is it so hard to do

826
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:47,520
one thing I really care about?

827
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:50,520
Take my advice.

828
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:51,640
Just let it go.

829
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:55,760
Secretary Peng is on a trip in Beijing.

830
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:56,640
Just now,

831
00:30:56,760 --> 00:30:58,960
she gave Deputy Mayor Luo a serious dressing-down.

832
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:00,160
Deputy Mayor Luo diverted

833
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:01,920
the special funds for the China Chic Zone.

834
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,240
That violates financial discipline.

835
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:05,840
Secretary Peng already knows the situation.

836
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,840
It'll be handled properly.

837
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:11,400
The problem now is,

838
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:13,920
the provincial funding process isn't done yet.

839
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:16,440
Secretary Peng wanted me to ask your opinion.

840
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,080
What are you thinking of doing next?

841
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:20,720
I'm tired.

842
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:23,240
Secretary Peng also said

843
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,960
this has really put you through a lot.

844
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,040
Whatever you decide,

845
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:29,720
she'll understand.

846
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,960
Honestly, I'm just not mature enough.

847
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:38,560
Director Liao often tells me

848
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:41,640
that nothing in this world

849
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:44,200
will bend to my will.

850
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:46,480
It's my problem.

851
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,240
Don't overthink it.

852
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:50,720
The China Chic Zone is cancelled,

853
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:52,720
but the Four Treasures Festival

854
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,400
still has to go on as planned.

855
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:56,720
Just do your best.

856
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:11,720
Little Lin's here.

857
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:12,560
Auntie Mei.

858
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:14,720
Long time no see, Little Lin.

859
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,760
Auntie Xu talks about you every day.

860
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:18,400
We've all missed you.

861
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,000
The other day we were joking,

862
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,720
saying Little Lin's become a big shot now,

863
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:22,520
hasn't come by in ages.

864
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:24,240
Maybe she looks down on us common folk?

865
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:24,840
No, no, no.

866
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:25,720
Shut that mouth of yours.

867
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:27,680
If you can't speak nicely, don't speak.

868
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,760
Little Lin's not like that, right?

869
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,720
It's really because work's been too busy.

870
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:32,720
I haven't had time to come.

871
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:33,720
It's my fault.

872
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:34,760
Are you all doing well?

873
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:35,400
Yes, yes, yes.

874
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,040
We're doing fine.

875
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:37,720
Auntie Xu heard you were coming,

876
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:39,520
so she made mugwort cakes for you

877
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,640
to take home.

878
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:41,720
Auntie Xu is the best to me.

879
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,240
Is Uncle Xuan inside?

880
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:43,800
Yes, yes, he's in there.

881
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:44,560
Go on, go on.

882
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:45,440
Let's chat later, later.

883
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,880
That Little Lin is really beautiful.

884
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:50,240
Look.

885
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:52,120
Little Lin.

886
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,440
Here.

887
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:54,920
Thank you, Auntie Xu.

888
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,000
It's hot.

889
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,040
Careful, hot!

890
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:09,280
Auntie, mugwort cakes in this season?

891
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:11,200
What's so strange about that?

892
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:13,920
You pick them in season,

893
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,120
and after picking,

894
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:17,200
blanch them and freeze them.

895
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,160
All year round,

896
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:20,400
whenever you want them, you can make them.

897
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:22,880
Little Lin,

898
00:33:24,120 --> 00:33:27,280
the booths are split into inner and outer areas?

899
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:31,320
The flagship Four Treasures companies

900
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:34,200
and national and provincial heritage inheritors

901
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:35,320
are all indoors.

902
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:36,760
The others are all outside.

903
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,680
Our booth

904
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:44,840
is pretty big.

905
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:45,560
Let me see.

906
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:46,320
Take a look.

907
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,000
That big, huh?

908
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:51,800
Who's next to us?

909
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:52,960
Hongxing Factory.

910
00:33:59,040 --> 00:33:59,880
How come we're...

911
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:03,080
How come we're placed next to them?

912
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,560
Can we switch?

913
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,560
The location doesn't really matter, right?

914
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,960
Just give us a different spot.

915
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,520
Even if it's outside,

916
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,120
or somewhere smaller, that's fine.

917
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:17,480
I don't really like being next to them.

918
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:18,679
Well...

919
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,320
The thing is, Secretary Peng assigned the spots.

920
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:23,159
All the placements have been finalized.

921
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:25,360
Besides, you're a national-level heritage inheritor.

922
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,760
It wouldn't be appropriate to put you outside.

923
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,520
There's nothing inappropriate about it.

924
00:34:28,679 --> 00:34:30,400
Of course it's inappropriate.

925
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,120
Old Xuan, think about it.

926
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:34,760
You're the Xuan paper heritage inheritor.

927
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:37,280
You're the face of Xuan paper.

928
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:39,360
How could we put you outside?

929
00:34:39,679 --> 00:34:40,760
You have to think about it.

930
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:41,840
When it works for you,

931
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:43,280
it also has to work for the government.

932
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:44,000
Right?

933
00:34:45,120 --> 00:34:45,920
Tell you what.

934
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,159
If it's not changed, you go.

935
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:49,960
I won't be going.

936
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,440
Uncle Xuan, you have to go.

937
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,000
Brush, ink, paper, and inkstone,

938
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:56,440
one national heritage master invited for each.

939
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,440
There'll be a grand master demonstration.

940
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,680
This event is hosted by Taohua Town.

941
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:02,040
You absolutely have to attend.

942
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:04,960
Xiao Lin,

943
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,640
consider this me begging you.

944
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:09,600
Get us a different spot.

945
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,360
If it's not changed,

946
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:13,600
I really won't go.

947
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:16,960
Alright.

948
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,400
I'll report back to Secretary Peng.

949
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,520
Thank you, thank you.

950
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:22,960
Sorry for the trouble.

951
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:23,680
Not at all.

952
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:25,840
By the way, Xiao Lin,

953
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:28,120
I heard from Xuan Yan

954
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:31,000
that you've hit a snag at work, right?

955
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:35,480
We were going to set up a China Chic Zone,

956
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:37,880
to attract a lot of young people.

957
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:41,600
But now it probably won't happen.

958
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,280
It's falling through?

959
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,160
What a shame.

960
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:48,960
If this had worked out,

961
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:51,920
many young people would come to love Xuan paper.

962
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,000
Such a pity.

963
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:58,120
The government has its own rules.

964
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,120
We shouldn't

965
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:01,480
be making comments about it.

966
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:05,680
Have some more.

967
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:06,200
Yes.

968
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:11,880
If you like it, come by anytime.

969
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:13,600
Thank you, Auntie.

970
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:18,480
Look, like this,

971
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,120
the ones with black charcoal spots,

972
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:21,240
have to be picked out.

973
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,000
And these darkened ones too.

974
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,920
None of these can be used. Sort them all out.

975
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:30,880
You're such a big director,

976
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:32,920
coming over here to help us.

977
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,960
Won't this hold up your real work?

978
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:38,000
It's fine.

979
00:36:38,120 --> 00:36:39,720
The China Chic Zone is off the table.

980
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:42,200
Everything else is already prepared.

981
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:45,480
That's good then.

982
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:49,240
Xiumei is so busy she has no time,

983
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:52,280
leaving just us two old-timers.

984
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:54,280
It's really a lot of work.

985
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,080
Xiao Lin,

986
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:00,920
take it easy.

987
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,920
Don't dwell on the unpleasant things.

988
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:07,520
In this lifetime,

989
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:11,480
as long as you believe what you're doing is right,

990
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:14,480
just do it, without wavering.

991
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,120
Of course,

992
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:21,000
that's not easy to do.

993
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,480
Yeah, Uncle Xuan.

994
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,600
That's why I really admire you.

995
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:31,120
I'm just an ordinary

996
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:32,800
papermaking worker.

997
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:35,400
There's nothing special to admire.

998
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:36,880
I can't speak on other matters,

999
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:41,240
but let me talk about our papermaking.

1000
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,720
A very long time ago,

1001
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:46,120
here in Taohua Town,

1002
00:37:46,720 --> 00:37:49,680
there were many Xuan paper family workshops.

1003
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:52,280
Take Erhu's Jiang family, for example.

1004
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:54,200
Back then, they did really well.

1005
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:56,400
But in the past two or three decades,

1006
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:59,600
fake Xuan paper started popping up.

1007
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:03,520
Erhu's family started faking their paper.

1008
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,960
Of course, he did it to make money.

1009
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,000
Actually, there's nothing wrong with that.

1010
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:10,680
Everyone wants to make money.

1011
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,600
But a gentleman earns wealth the right way.

1012
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,520
You can't just, because

1013
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:19,120
the blue sandalwood bark got expensive,

1014
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:22,000
switch to dragon-beard grass instead.

1015
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:26,200
Then grass gets pricey, so you switch to bamboo pulp.

1016
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:29,480
Bamboo pulp gets pricey, so you switch to wood pulp.

1017
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:34,280
Whatever makes money, that's what he does.

1018
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:38,680
Few people out there really know Xuan paper.

1019
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,680
So they go against their conscience,

1020
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,960
doing things that hurt others for their own gain,

1021
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:46,200
utterly devoid of any morals.

1022
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,880
Passing off fakes as real,

1023
00:38:49,280 --> 00:38:51,280
passing off inferior as premium.

1024
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:54,640
The fine things our ancestors passed down,

1025
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:56,840
they've thrown into the outhouse.

1026
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,080
Uncle Xuan,

1027
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:03,520
I'd like to ask you a question.

1028
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:06,240
You've held on for so many years.

1029
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:09,000
Has reality never gotten the better of you?

1030
00:39:09,720 --> 00:39:12,880
It depends on what you want in this life.

1031
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,200
Take Erhu, for instance.

1032
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:19,440
He threw away the heritage,

1033
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,080
and got money in exchange.

1034
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,880
I didn't make much money,

1035
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:28,480
but I didn't betray my ancestors.

1036
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,280
Of course, in my hardest times,

1037
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,600
I did hesitate.

1038
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:34,600
Why couldn't I be like them?

1039
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,280
Just close my eyes

1040
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,480
and go make money.

1041
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,680
What's the harm? Who cares?

1042
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:41,480
But then I thought about it.

1043
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:43,240
No.

1044
00:39:44,240 --> 00:39:45,120
I don't dare.

1045
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:47,600
I can't do that.

1046
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:49,920
Why not?

1047
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:53,600
Because you're a national intangible heritage inheritor,

1048
00:39:54,040 --> 00:39:55,200
the heir of the Xuan family.

1049
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,920
What is heritage, really?

1050
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:02,600
Heritage isn't just learning a craft.

1051
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:06,640
More important than the craft itself

1052
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:10,120
is the virtue of being human.

1053
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,480
If you can't be a decent person,

1054
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:13,800
then your paper,

1055
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:15,600
you certainly won't make it well.

1056
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,080
Only when you achieve both

1057
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:20,800
have you truly received the heritage.

1058
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,120
You're right to hold on.

1059
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:27,720
No, no, no.

1060
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:29,880
Maybe what I'm doing

1061
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,120
won't turn out well.

1062
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:34,960
But for me,

1063
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:37,080
in my whole life,

1064
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:38,920
I won't regret doing this.

1065
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:42,520
But Uncle Xuan,

1066
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,840
you've inspired me.

1067
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:48,480
I want to learn from you.

1068
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:51,480
No matter how many hardships come,

1069
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:53,120
we should stay true to ourselves,

1070
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:55,680
and keep walking the path we believe in.

1071
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:56,960
Right.

1072
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,120
Okay, you two carry on then.

1073
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,320
Uncle Xuan, I'm heading off.

1074
00:40:59,720 --> 00:41:00,240
Bye.

1075
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:01,200
I'll come help you again later.

1076
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:02,640
See you.

1077
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:12,240
I was counting on young folks' sharp eyes

1078
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:14,120
to get more done.

1079
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:16,720
Five minutes of sorting,

1080
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,920
five minutes of chatting,

1081
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,120
and off she goes.

1082
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:20,360
Enough.

1083
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:22,840
You expect young people to stick with

1084
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:25,600
work that even we have to be patient for?

1085
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,840
It's normal that she left.

1086
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:32,520
Just us two old-timers, taking it slow.

1087
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,680
Stop grumbling.

1088
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,000
Xuan Yan.

1089
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,320
What's this?

1090
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:48,280
A paper boat.

1091
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,480
Didn't I say before

1092
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:52,080
I wanted to make a boat out of Xuan paper?

1093
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,240
Is that weird?

1094
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:56,480
Won't a paper boat just sink in water?

1095
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,480
Something that sinks is called a submarine,

1096
00:41:58,480 --> 00:41:59,400
not a boat.

1097
00:41:59,920 --> 00:42:02,400
Only a weirdo would do something this weird.

1098
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:04,680
Let me talk to you about something serious.

1099
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:05,880
The China Chic Zone -

1100
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:07,520
all the AR-designed scenes,

1101
00:42:07,520 --> 00:42:08,520
I'm planning to scrap them all.

1102
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:10,280
Replace them with traditional Chinese scenes,

1103
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:11,520
but the kind that don't cost much.

1104
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:12,240
Can it be done?

1105
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,000
Trying to get something for nothing?

1106
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:15,520
Just talk properly.

1107
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:17,480
Hurry, help me figure out how much I can save.

1108
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,720
The equipment you were going to rent

1109
00:42:19,720 --> 00:42:21,520
was around one hundred thousand plus.

1110
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:22,800
If we swap it all for what you're saying...

1111
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:23,880
Wait, wait, wait.

1112
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:25,640
The low-cost kind.

1113
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,200
Just like you said,

1114
00:42:27,200 --> 00:42:29,200
design it in the low-cost way.

1115
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:32,200
If we switch to those Chinese-style scenes,

1116
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,880
plus the unfinished work from before,

1117
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,840
it'd be around fifty thousand, give or take.

1118
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,400
Then starting tomorrow,

1119
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:42,800
would four days be enough?

1120
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:44,000
Others can't,

1121
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,120
but I can.

1122
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,520
I need to discuss something with you.

1123
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:50,560
Go ahead.

1124
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,320
About this portion of the cost -

1125
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:55,800
could you front the money first?

1126
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:57,840
Once we turn a profit, I'll pay you back.
